        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <head>237. Message From Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="from"
                        >Macmillan</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1" type="to"
                        >Eisenhower</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d237fn1">Source: Eisenhower Library, Whitman
                        File, International File. Top Secret. Transmitted under cover of a note from
                            <persName corresp="#p_CSHA1">Caccia</persName> to <persName
                            corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, dated March 31.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1957</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Friend</hi>: Thank you for your letter about
                    Archbishop Makarios.<note n="2" xml:id="d237fn2">See telegram 6822, <ref
                            target="#d236">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> As you say, this was a difficult decision for us and you will
                    have seen that it was not taken without loss to the Government. I do not believe
                    that the Archbishop has changed his views in the Seychelles; he is the Bourbon
                    of Cyprus. But events in the island <pb facs="0500" n="470" xml:id="pg_470"/>
                    and in the world are surging past him. <persName corresp="#p_HFMSJ1"
                        >Harding</persName> has beaten terrorism militarily, and the world now
                    recognizes that Cyprus is an international problem.</p>
                <p>I am sure that your aid in persuading all concerned to face reality could be of
                    decisive help. Of course my right-wing assume that we released the Archbishop at
                    your request, so private pressure by you would be better than public
                    statements.</p>
                <p>Warm regards, as ever,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Harold Macmillan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d237fn3">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                        signature.</note>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
